Fun fact: Good design can save lives.The myResponder mobile app alerts nearby members of the public to incidents like fires and cardiac arrest cases, helping first responders act fast. The second version of the app, which was launched on July 4, 2024, led to a 23% increase in signups and a 56%80% boost in first responder arrival rates.On 25 Nov, myResponder clinched the Singapore Good Design (SG Mark) distinction award (Gold), which recognises companies and individuals who have generated positive impact through solutions that focus on human needs and experiences.Kudos to HTXs Digital Services Programme Management Centre and the Singapore Civil Defence Force (SCDF) for co-developing this life-saving tool!

New Psychoactive Substances (NPS) are rapidly evolving, and so is Singapores response to this challenge. NPS are chemically engineered compounds designed to mimic the effects of illicit drugs, which can lead to potentially fatal consequences. These substances are often more difficult to detect using conventional methods and can evade existing laws, creating new challenges for authorities and society. HTXs FIRST (Forensic Innovation and Research for Strategic Transformation) Lab utilises advanced technology and forensic science to analyse unknown substances and understand their effects on the human body. This research helps authorities stay ahead of the growing threat posed by NPS. Find out more about how the FIRST Lab is contributing to Singapores fight against NPS on our website, link in bio.

The backpack on its back gently interacts with the insects movement, allowing researchers to study and enhance navigation in tight spaces where conventional miniaturised robots often struggle. HTX has trained a series of artificial intelligence (AI) language models for the Home Team called Phoenix. These large language models (LLMs) understand Singapores unique context and multicultural environment. Phoenix, developed in collaboration with Mistral AI and Microsoft, supports 10 languages, including English, Chinese, Malay, and Tamil. Phoenix is a key part of HTXs AI strategy, laying the foundation for developing AI applications tailored to the Home Team, said HTX Chief AI Officer and Assistant Chief Executive (Digital and Enterprise) Ang Chee Wee. In an interview with Lianhe Zaobao, AI engineers Arka Ray and Wang Jia Le from HTXs Q Team shared that Phoenix was developed to help Home Team officers complete daily tasks more efficiently, allowing them to focus on critical, high-value work. Unlike global AI models, Phoenix understands Singapores local context by recognising and processing uniquely Singaporean acronyms and terminology. Built with billions of tokens of training data, its designed to enhance Home Team operations while maintaining the highest data security and output standards. This achievement represents another milestone in HTXs mission to empower our Home Team officers with cutting-edge technology, enabling them to focus on high-value tasks while improving operational efficiency. Read more: HTXsg OneHomeTeam HTxAI

Demo Days for Dimension X, the flagship innovation programme by Hatch, HTXs innovation centre for public safety, are always exciting. Demo Day for Cohort 5 of Dimension X on 31 July 2025 was no exception.We were honoured to welcome Mr , Minister for Law and Second Minister for Home Affairs, as our Guest of Honour, alongside Home Team officers, international start-ups, and partners.From a competitive pool of more than 270 global applications, 11 cutting-edge start-ups from 6 countries were selected to co-develop and validate bold proofs-of-concepts alongside challenge owners from HTX and the Home Team.Over the past few months, these collaborations tackled real operational challenges across the Home Team, with innovations in: Embodied AI for multifunctional robotics Spectral imaging to identify hazardous compounds Real-time video enhancement in rainy weather Drone detection of unconventional materials LLM/LMM data curation tools Video compression for low-bandwidth environments Information extraction from unstructured dataIn his opening address, Mr Tong encouraged everyone to think of Demo Days as going beyond showcases to be launch pads.Through Hatch, we continue to scout and accelerate global dual-use technologies, transforming how the Home Team keeps Singapore safe all the way from the frontlines to the back end.HTXsg DimensionX
